Durban - A man on trial for rape and robbery at the Umhlali Court, north of Durban, made a dash for freedom after jumping over the courtroom counter and fleeing towards a train station. The 25-year-old escaped at about 10.30am, said police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane. Witnesses claimed he had boarded a KwaDukuza-bound train. *Anyone who knows his whereabouts is urged to call Umhlali police at 032 947 9925 or Crime Stop at 08600 10111. Daily News